==English==
===Etymology===
From its capability of ''looking down'' from the intercepting aircraft to the ground and then ''shooting down'' the enemy.

===Adjective===
'''look-down, shoot-down'''

====Variant forms====
'''look-down shoot-down''', '''look-down/shoot-down''', '''look down/shoot down'''; ''also, non-standardly, without hyphens''

